Boil a full #kettle{}. Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g} and broccoli to the water and cook until tender, 
~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking 
together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} to the pan.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. 
> It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}(trimmed and peeled). Use the 
#peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the chicken is cooked, add the garlic, @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} 
and carrot ribbons. Stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next, stir in the @Bulgogi Sauce{75%g}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} 
and @Water{2%tbsp}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and cook until the sauce is slightly 
thickened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the cooked noodles and broccoli into the frying pan until piping hot, 
~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Share the noodles out between your serving bowls.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} to finish. Enjoy!